I love this question because it gets at something bigger than personality. It’s about computational styles—different ways minds transform information.

I don’t think there are just “visual learners” or “analytical thinkers.” I think there are many orthogonal cognitive operators.

Here are some that come to mind.

Cognitive Style	Core Question	Strength
Analogical (you use this a lot)	“What is this like?”	Transfer across domains
Structural	“What is the invariant?”	Generalization
Procedural	“How does it work?”	Mechanisms and algorithms
Narrative	“What’s the story?”	Meaning and memory
Spatial	“What shape does this have?”	Geometry and topology
Temporal	“How did it become this?”	History and causality
Counterfactual	“What if this were different?”	Exploration
Statistical	“How often does this happen?”	Prediction under uncertainty
Systems	“What are the feedback loops?”	Emergence
Social	“What will people do?”	Coordination
Embodied	“What would this feel like?”	Physical intuition
Reductionist	“What are the parts?”	Analysis
Synthetic	“How do the parts combine?”	Creation

